The State, Respondent, vs. Guenther and others, Appellants.

[Second case.]

April 16 May 1, 1894. APPEAL from the Circuit Court for Dane County. For the appellants there was a brief by Thompsons, Harshaw da Davidson, and oral argument by A. E. Thompson. The Attorney General, for the respondent. Newman, J.

The question in this case is the same as that in the preceding case, ante, p. 673. The judgment must be affirmed for the reason given in that case.

By the Court.— The judgment of the circuit court is affirmed.

Pinney, 3., took no part.
